UGHELLI – A 44-year-old mother of three simply identified as Mrs. Tina Etameta has been kidnapped by suspected kidnappers at Ughelli in Ughelli North North Local Government Area of Delta State. According to a family source, Tina, was kidnapped at her shop opposite Agbarha-OtorJunction where she sells provisions at about 8 pm on Monday, January 4, 2021. It would be recalled that a generator mechanic, Kelly Asaboro, was shot dead by suspected armed robbers within the same area last week on New Year’s Eve. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The source disclosed that the suspected hoodlums arrived the shop amidst sporadic shooting to whisk away their target to an unknown destination. The husband, Mr. Lucky Etemata, who spoke to DAILY INDEPENDENT, said, “While the hoodlums were shooting, I had to escape and my wife that ran into the shop was followed by the masked men and she was taken away.” Foundation Wants More Support For Widows Democrats Poised To Control US Senate, Giving Biden Upper Hand All efforts to contact the Delta State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Onome Onowakpoyeya, were not successful but a senior police officer attached to the Ughelli Area Command confirmed the incident. He said that security agents are on the trail of the kidnappers. As of the time of this report no contact or channel of communication with the family has been opened.